                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Except mentioning that in the migration chapter, we could also allow escaping special chars (being colon \":\" and at \"@\" in the beginning of a segment). Thus you would be able to use them again without a dirty workaround.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
